#: ../../../release/1.13.1-notes.rst:3
msgid "NumPy 1.13.1 Release Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.13.1-notes.rst:5
msgid ""
"This is a bugfix release for problems found in 1.13.0. The major changes are "
"fixes for the new memory overlap detection and temporary elision as well as "
"reversion of the removal of the boolean binary ``-`` operator. Users of "
"1.13.0 should upgrade."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.13.1-notes.rst:10
msgid ""
"Thr Python versions supported are 2.7 and 3.4 - 3.6. Note that the Python "
"3.6 wheels available from PIP are built against 3.6.1, hence will not work "
"when used with 3.6.0 due to Python bug 29943_. NumPy 1.13.2 will be released "
"shortly after Python 3.6.2 is out to fix that problem. If you are using "
"3.6.0 the workaround is to upgrade to 3.6.1 or use an earlier Python version."
msgstr ""

